text: Nadine Thomas (born May 14, 1952) is an American politician who served in the Georgia House of Representatives from the 55th district from 1991 to 1993 and in the Georgia State Senate from the 10th district from 1993 to 2005. ==References== Category:1952 births Category:Living people Category:Members of the Georgia House of Representatives Category:Georgia (U.S. state) state senators Category:Georgia (U.S. state) Democrats Category:African-American state legislators in Georgia (U.S. state)
